This script will compile dedicated server and UDP masterserver,
and put both of them into current user's crontab to run at boot.
It should be run on a fresh Debian installation.
It will also install all necessary packages using sudo -
it expects passwordless sudo, such as inside the Docker container,
so you need to enter the password once, or run it as root,
in which case the dedicated server will run with root privileges,
which is not secure and not recommended.
It will also install Python 2, required for dedicated scripts.

OpenLieroX must be copied to directory $HOME/openlierox.
This script should be run from the Git root directory.

cd $HOME
git clone https://github.com/openlierox/openlierox -b 0.58
cd $HOME/openlierox
tools/DedicatedServerSetupDebian/setup.sh

sudo reboot
